Max standardised gap (Cohen's d) across moments, vs nu:
  nu=0.05  max d =  5.01  <- FW 2012 value
  nu=0.1   max d =  4.91
  nu=0.3   max d =  4.88
  nu=1.0   max d =  0.17  <- TPA -> DCA limit

Reading: the faithful DCA/TPA pair separates strongly on standard
moments wherever it is dynamically distinct (large d at nu <= 0.30),
and is confusable only as nu -> 1 where TPA collapses into DCA (d small).
So moments already capture the behavioural difference; this is the
premise of Finding 1. The matched-moment test in which nonlinear
features could matter is constructed against a GARCH null instead
(experiment/harder_pair.py).
